<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870310-0163 </DOCNO><HL> Energy Assets PurchasesStake in Natural Gas Fields</HL><DD> 03/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EAIC GOPNATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Energy Assets International Corp. said it completed its previously announced acquisition of half of Graham-McCormick Oil andamp; Gas Partnership's interest in two Texas natural gas fields for $21 million.    Graham-McCormick, a Covington, La., oil and gas limited partnership, said it would use about $20 million of the proceeds to pay the principal of its senior secured notes. Graham-McCormick said its scheduled semiannual principal payments on the remaining $40 million of notes have been satisfied until December 1988.    As previously reported, Energy Assets bought about a 30% interest in the Oak Hill field in Rusk County and a 25% interest in the Carter Ranch field in Brooks County. Energy Assets is a financing company for oil and gas operators. </TEXT></DOC>